Value = 8bit@byte2, MinValue=-99, MaxValue=99, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Signed, Reference=None, Hint=Cent range

;-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[$23]
Type = Special
Name = SETUP TREMOLO
Icon =mapto.ico

MainHint=Configure tremolo effect scale (DLS). This scale is applied to the output of LFO1. This LFO is the source for the tremolo waveform. The 1st parameter defines a base scale to be used. The second scale is used to scale the modulation wheel input. The result will be added to the first parameter to form th final scale.

ShortHint=Scale LFO1 with scale add modulatin wheel scaled by 2nd scale. Use value to modulate volume.

Value = 16bit@byte1, MinValue=0, MaxValue=16383, PresetValue=8192, Type=VAL_Normal, Reference=None, Hint=Tremolo scale
Value = 16bit@byte4, MinValue=0, MaxValue=16383, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Normal, Reference=None, Hint=Modw. add scale

