[$50]
Type = Setup
Name = SETUP_LFO
Icon =wave.ico

Mainhint=Enables or disables the specified LFO. A value of zero as period will disable the LFO. From that point on it will continue to produce the last value as a constant. The LFO will always start at center level, unless it already was active. The LFO Nr. specifies which LFO should be setup. Currently two LFOs (0,1) are supported. The LFOs always swing through the full amplitude. Use the scale parameter when combining them by one or more x_SELECT commands to control the amplitude. The LFOs are mapped to the internal controller numbers 130 (LFO 0) and 131 (LFO 1).

Shorthint=Setup LFO

Value = 8bit@byte1, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Normal, Reference=None , Hint=LFO Nr.
Value = 16bit@byte2, MinValue=-10000, MaxValue=10000, PresetValue=100, Type=VAL_Normal, Reference=None, Hint=Period in ms

