ShortHint=Send a keyoff

Value = 8bit@byte1, MinValue=0, MaxValue=31, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_NORMAL, Reference=None , Hint=Variable
Value = 8bit@byte2, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_SWITCH, Reference=None , Hint=Last started

;-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[$07]
Type = Structure
Name = WAIT_MS
Icon =wait.ico

MainHint=The execution of the current macro will be suspendet until the given time is over. By default the time is specified in ms. A value of $FFFF (65535) will cause an endless wait. If one of the other flags is set the execution will resument as soon as one of the corresponding conditions gets true or the time given is over. Key Release - Wait until a keyoff is send to the macro. Sampleend - Wait until the sample has reached its end. Random - The time will be used as a maximum to get a randomized delay.

ShortHint=Wait, depending on different conditions

Value = 8bit@byte1, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=1, Type=VAL_Switch, Reference=None, Hint=Keyoff
Value = 8bit@byte2, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Switch, Reference=None, Hint=Random
Value = 8bit@byte3, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Switch, Reference=None, Hint=Sample end
Value = 8bit@byte4, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Switch, Reference=None, Hint=Absolute
Value = 16bit@byte6, MinValue=0, MaxValue=65535, PresetValue=65535, Type=VAL_Normal, Reference=None, Hint=Millisec.

;-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[$04]
Type = Structure
Name = WAIT_TICKS
Icon =wait.ico

MainHint=The execution of the current macro will be suspended until the given time is elapsed. By default, the time is specified in ticks. If the millisec flag is set the time will be specified in ms. Independent from the selected time format a value of $FFFF (65535) will cause an endless wait. If one of the other flags is set the execution will resument as soon as one of the corresponding conditions gets true or the time given is over. Key Release - Wait until a keyoff is send to the macro. Sampleend - Wait until the sample has reached its end. Random - The time will be used as a maximum to get a randomized delay.

ShortHint=Wait, depending on different conditions

Value = 8bit@byte1, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Switch, Reference=None, Hint=Keyoff
Value = 8bit@byte2, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Switch, Reference=None, Hint=Random
Value = 8bit@byte3, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Switch, Reference=None, Hint=Sampleend
Value = 8bit@byte4, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Switch, Reference=None, Hint=Absolute
Value = 8bit@byte5, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Switch, Reference=None, Hint=ms switch
Value = 16bit@byte6, MinValue=0, MaxValue=65535, PresetValue=96, Type=VAL_Normal, Reference=None, Hint=Ticks/Millisec.

;-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[$05]
Type = Structure
Name = LOOP
Icon =loop.ico

MainHint=Loop to the specified location within the current macro times times. If one of the flags is set the loop may be executed less than the specified number of times. A value of $FFFF (65535) will cause an endless loop. Key Release - Loop until a keyoff is send to the macro. Sampleend - Loop until the sample has reached its end. Random - The number of loops will be used as a maximum to get a randomized counter.

ShortHint=Loop back to a macrostep

Value = 8bit@byte1, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Switch, Reference=None, Hint=Keyoff
Value = 8bit@byte2, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Switch, Reference=None, Hint=Random
Value = 8bit@byte3, MinValue=0, MaxValue=1, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Switch, Reference=None, Hint=Sampleend
Value = 16bit@byte4, MinValue=0, MaxValue=65535, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Normal, Reference=SoundMacroLoopStep, Hint=SoundMacro step
Value = 16bit@byte6, MinValue=0, MaxValue=65535, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Normal, Reference=None, Hint=Times

;-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[$08]
Type = Structure
Name = PLAYMACRO
Icon =play.ico

MainHint=Starts another macro in parallel to the current one. Since it will be started like any other macro the normal delays etc. apply. The macro will be passed the priority and the maxvoices value specified. The key is calculated by adding addnote to the current key of the macro starting the new one. The new macro may be started at any macrostep using the step parameter.

ShortHint=Starts another macro

Value = 8bit@byte1, MinValue=-128, MaxValue=127, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_SIGNED, Reference=None , Hint=Addnote
Value = 16bit@byte2, MinValue=0, MaxValue=65535, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_SoundMacroID, Reference=SoundMacro, Hint=SoundMacro ID
Value = 16bit@byte4, MinValue=0, MaxValue=65535, PresetValue=0, Type=VAL_Normal, Reference=SoundMacroStep, Hint=SoundMacro step
Value = 8bit@byte6, MinValue=0, MaxValue=127, PresetValue=50, Type=VAL_Normal, Reference=None , Hint=Priority
Value = 8bit@byte7, MinValue=0, MaxValue=255, PresetValue=255, Type=VAL_Normal, Reference=None , Hint=MaxVoices

